"content": "<h2>A lawyer as a person skilled in the Mosaic law</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:35\">MAT 22:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:30\">LUK 7:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:25\">LUK 10:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:37\">LUK 10:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:45-Luke11:46\">LUK 11:45–11:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:52\">LUK 11:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:3\">LUK 14:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:13\">TIT 3:13</a></p>\n<h2>A lawyer as a person trained in rhetoric</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:1\">ACT 24:1</a> <em>The word translated “lawyer” means literally “orator”: a person trained in rhetoric who served as an attorney-at-law in a court trial.</em></p>",
